        title: "Join a Local Club and an Online Community",
        content: "Solo ham radio is fun, but the real reward is the community. Most cities and counties have at least one club, listed at ARRL.org under Clubs. Meetings happen monthly and usually feature a short talk, a club business segment, and a coffee-and-cookies social hour. Dues run 20 to 50 dollars a year. Online forums such as eHam.net, QRZ.com, and Reddit's r/amateurradio give 24-hour access to questions and answers from operators worldwide. Veterans groups host the Military Auxiliary Radio System, or MARS, for licensed operators who served. Many seniors find a lifelong mentor, called an Elmer, through a club. The Elmer relationship pairs a new operator with a seasoned one for guidance on equipment, technique, and the path to General and Extra licenses.",
